1:1 COMMENT "# generator_counter.z -- minimal no-argument generator."
1:56 EOL "\n"
2:1 COMMENT "#"
2:2 EOL "\n"
3:1 COMMENT "# `counter` takes no parameters; it just yields the first three"
3:64 EOL "\n"
4:1 COMMENT "# positive integers. Calling it bare (`for x: counter loop ...`)"
4:65 EOL "\n"
5:1 COMMENT "# is auto-invoked by the typechecker: when a for-loop's iterable"
5:65 EOL "\n"
6:1 COMMENT "# resolves to a 0-arg function returning an iterator class, the"
6:64 EOL "\n"
7:1 COMMENT "# typechecker rewrites the condition to a synthetic"
7:52 EOL "\n"
8:1 COMMENT "# `Call(callable=<fn>, arguments=[])` so the existing"
8:54 EOL "\n"
9:1 COMMENT "# callable-object dispatch handles the rest."
9:45 EOL "\n"
10:1 COMMENT "#"
10:2 EOL "\n"
11:1 COMMENT "# The bare reference form is the canonical no-arg generator"
11:60 EOL "\n"
12:1 COMMENT "# idiom -- equivalent to `for x: (counter) loop ...` (paren"
12:60 EOL "\n"
13:1 COMMENT "# form). Both compile to the same C."
13:37 EOL "\n"
14:1 EOL "\n"
